<TEXT>
<P>
Around 250 hard-line Muslims have staged a demonstration warning Pakistan's president not to pardon a Christian woman sentenced to death for insulting Islam.
</P>
<P>
The rally in the city of Lahore also defended the blasphemy law that critics say is often misused to persecute minorities.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's protest is a snapshot of emotions that have swirled around Asia Bibi -- the Christian woman whose case has prompted outrage from human rights groups and a personal appeal from Pope Benedict XVI for her release.
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old mother of five has said she was falsely accused by a group of Muslim women in a personal dispute.
</P>
<P>
Bibi has been jailed in Punjab province since her arrest 18 months ago.
</P>
<P>
A court sentenced her earlier in November to death by hanging.
