February 1956

As &quot;Heartbreak Hotel&quot; made it's climb up the charts on it's way to number 1, &quot;I Forgot To Remember To Forget&quot; b/w &quot;Mystery Train&quot;, Elvis' fifth and last single to be released on the Sun label hit number 1 on Billboards national Country singles chart. His first number 1 hit on a national chart.

