</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's Chief Justice Wang Shengjun said Thursday that courts will take actions
on judicial corruption to prevent abuse of judicial power after a former vice
president of the supreme court was jailed for life two months ago.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court (SPC) will "strengthen capacity building and act as a
model for local courts," Wang, SPC president, told nearly 3,000 lawmakers at the
annual parliament session when delivering a work report.
</P>
<P>
The pledge came after Huang Songyou, former SPC vice president, was sentenced on
Jan. 19 to life imprisonment for taking bribes and embezzlement.
</P>
<P>
